article.headline: Portland 82, Idaho 52
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Jared Stohl scored 30 points on a school-record 10 3-pointers to lead Portland to an 82-52 victory over Idaho on Tuesday night. The victory represented a 50-point turnaround for the Pilots (7-4), who earlier in the season lost a 20-point decision on the Vandals' home court. That loss helped knock Portland out of the Associated Press Top 25. Mac Hopson scored 15 points to lead Idaho (6-4). Stohl finished Tuesday's game 10 of 15 from the 3-point line. He had only two shots from inside the line and missed both. He also wound up with career-highs in rebounds (six) and steals (three). Stohl fell three points short of a career high in points, which came last year against San Francisco, when he set the previous school record with nine 3-pointers.
